page_summary: This page describes risk factors, etiology, and diagnostic workflows for breast cancer, emphasizing the importance of collecting subject and disease characteristics at clinical trial entry, such as age at diagnosis, date of diagnosis, and methods of diagnosis (self-assessment, clinical exams, imaging, biopsy, and pathology). It outlines the relevance of these collected data for stratification, eligibility, and analysis in breast cancer trials but does not provide concrete definitions or operationalization of clinical trial endpoints.
